A suspect described by police as a notorious robber on Wednesday night was gunned down at Musikoma, Bungoma town. A rifle was recovered. Naftali Mung&rsquo;eri was shot by Flying Squad officers who had been on his trail for four months.&ldquo;We thank God his 40 days came: he has been giving residents sleepless nights,&rdquo; Bungoma South OCPD David Kirui said.Mung&rsquo;eri was cornered near Nabongo Teachers&rsquo; College. Kirui said Mung&rsquo;eri was involved in kidnappings and major robberies. He thanked the public for giving information on Mung&rsquo;eri&rsquo;s whereabouts and called for more cooperation to reduce crime.